
@startuml
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam noteStyle rectangle

' Define classes and their attributes
class Person {
  +personID: String
  +phone: String
  +keywords: List<String>
  +institutionCode: String
}

class Institution {
  +institutionCode: String
  +name: String
}

class Article {
  +doi: String
  +title: String
  +authors: List<Person>
  +authorPositions: List<Integer>
  +isPeerReviewed: Boolean
}

class PeerReviewedArticle extends Article {
  +citationCount: Integer
  +reviewers: List<Person>
}

class TechnicalReport extends Article {
  +publisher: Institution
}

class Publisher {
  +name: String
  +journals: List<Journal>
}

class Journal {
  +name: String
  +impactFactor: Double
  +publisher: Publisher
}

' Relationships
Person --|> Institution : worksFor (1 to 1)
Article "1" --o"*" Person : authoredBy (1 to many)
Article "1" --o"*" Person : reviewedBy (only for peer-reviewed articles)
Institution --|> TechnicalReport : publishedBy (1 to many)
Publisher --|> Journal : publishes (1 to many)
Journal --|> PeerReviewedArticle : contains (1 to many)

note right of Article
  Articles can be either
  PeerReviewedArticle or
  TechnicalReport
end note

@enduml

### Explanation:
- **Person**: Represents a researcher. Attributes include `personID`, `phone`, `keywords`, and `institutionCode`.
- **Institution**: Represents a research institution. Each has an `institutionCode` and a `name`.
- **Article**: Base class for all scientific articles. Has a `doi`, `title`, list of authors, author positions, and a flag indicating if it's peer-reviewed.
- **PeerReviewedArticle**: Subclass of `Article`. Has `citationCount` and a list of `reviewers`.
- **TechnicalReport**: Subclass of `Article`. Is always published by one `Institution`.
- **Publisher**: Stores information about publishers (e.g., Elsevier). Can have multiple `Journals`.
- **Journal**: Contains a name, impact factor, and is associated with a `Publisher`. Only contains `PeerReviewedArticle`s.

